widgets.title: TTFS (median)
widgets.description: Time To First Sound average duration, from final speech transcript to first sound received in the client

widgets.title: TTFCT (avg)
widgets.description: Time To First Coherent Thought (average) - the first "coherent thought" is the first LLM-generated thought that can be sent to the Text To Speech (TTS) for audio generation

widgets.title: TTFChk (avg)
widgets.description: Time To First Chunk (average) - the "first chunk" is the first response from the LLM

widgets.title: STT Latency
widgets.description: Speech To Text latency over time

widgets.title: TTS Latency
widgets.description: Text To Speech (Elevenlabs) latency over time

widgets.title: Max Active Connections
widgets.description: Number of currently active connections. Reporting delayed by 60 seconds.

widgets.title: Conversations  by turn count and interruptions

dataprimeQuery.text:
source logs
| filter $d.log_obj.turn_id > 2
| create $d.time_bucket from roundTime($m.timestamp, 12h)
| groupby $d.time_bucket aggregate count_if($d.log_obj.interruption == true) as interruptionCount, count_if($d.log_obj.interruption == false) as nonInterruptionCount
| create $d.interruptRate from $d.interruptionCount / ($d.interruptionCount + $d.nonInterruptionCount)
source logs | filter log_obj.turn_id > 2 | filter log_obj.event == 'interruption' | groupby log_obj.conversation_id | count
source logs | filter log_obj.turn_id > 2 | groupby log_obj.conversation_id | count

source logs | filter log_obj.turn_id > 2
| groupby log_obj.conversation_id, log_obj.event
| groupby log_obj.conversation_id aggregate count_if(log_obj.event=='interruption') as interruptCount
| aggregate count(log_obj.conversation_id) as denominator, sum(interruptCount) as numerator
| add result from numerator/denominator
| select result * 100

widgets.title: Interrupted Speaking Spans by Duration (Interruption Offset)

dataprimeQuery.text:
source spans
| filter $l.operationName == 'client-speech'
| filter tags.interrupted == true
| create bucket from case {
    duration < 100000 -> '< 100ms',
    duration < 500000 -> '100-500ms',
    duration < 1000000 -> '500-1000ms',
    duration < 2000000 -> '1000-2000ms',
    _ -> '2000+ms'
}
| groupby bucket aggregate count() as bucket_count
